HEADWORD: Popularize
<hw>Pop"u*lar*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Popularized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Popularizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>populariser</ets>.]</ety> <def>To make popular; to make suitable
or acceptable to the common people; to make generally known; <as>as, to
<ex>popularize</ex> philosophy</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>popularizing</xex> of religious teaching.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
